Unit testing:
-------------

1. TDD /BDD - Test Driven approach - No need to have application created first.
2. Application + Tests

Writing Unittestcase requiers two things:
-----------------------------------------

1. Testing frameworks - Eg : Jasmine - provides Tesing API from javascript perspectives
        Define/write the TestSuites - collection of testcases/related testcases.

2. Tesing engine - Execution of test cases - - Eg: Karma


Steps :

    1. Install karma and Jasmine
        npm i karma jasmine-core karma-jasmine
    2. Install karma-cli as globally - gives u karma.exe file 
    3. Creation of karma config file. - karma.conf.js
    4. karma init
    5. karma start

    Karma test case debug : default browser with debug option will open

    click on debug -> inspect the page select base folder under sources tab

    
Express : Rapid application developement and abstraction of node
--------

Its a middleware or framework - working on top of node

1. Routing
2. Rendering - engine (Handlebar)
3. session management
4. Cookies